text: The Medical Journal of Australia is a peer-reviewed medical journal. It is the official journal of the Australian Medical Association and began in 1914. It is published by the Australasian Medical Publishing Company Proprietary Limited (AMPCo). The journal publishes editorials, articles, case reports, and letters. The full text of every issue since January 2002 is available on their website. ==Related pages== * British Medical Journal *The Lancet == References == ==Other websites== * Category:Medical journals Category:Newspapers published in Australia
